                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-date&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;comment-link&quot; href=&quot;#comment91666647_46264011&quot;&gt;&lt;span title=&quot;2018-09-17 05:24:30Z, License: CC BY-SA 4.0&quot; class=&quot;relativetime-clean&quot;&gt;Sep 17, 2018 at 5:24&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@melpomene Yes that would be direct and good.  Yet if the &lt;code&gt;break&lt;/code&gt; was not there,  &lt;code&gt;i++&lt;/code&gt; would occur and the following &lt;code&gt;Name[i]&lt;/code&gt; would be 0,  stopping the loop.  Your good idea has the advantage of &lt;code&gt;i&lt;/code&gt; being the string length after the loop.&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/2410359/chux-reinstate-monica&quot; title=&quot;128,313 reputation&quot; class=&quot;comment-user&quot;&gt;chux - Reinstate Monica&lt;/a&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
